# ðŸ§­ Cybersecurity Career Pathway

A structured overview of cybersecurity job roles, organised by career level. Use this roadmap to track progression, align certifications, and plan strategic upskilling.

---

## ðŸ”¹ Feeder Roles *(Foundational Entry Points)*

These roles build transferable skills that feed into cybersecurity specialisations:

- Networking  
- Software Development  
- System Engineering  
- Financial Risk Analysis  
- Security Intelligence  

> ðŸ’¡ Tip: Pair these roles with foundational certifications like CompTIA ITF+, Network+, or basic programming courses.

---

## ðŸŸ¢ Entry-Level Roles *(Launchpad for Cyber Careers)*

Ideal for newcomers with basic certifications and hands-on lab experience:

- Cybersecurity Technician  
- Cyber Crime Investigator  
- Incident Analyst / Responder  
- IT Auditor  

> ðŸŽ¯ Recommended Certs: CompTIA Security+, ISC2 Certified in Cybersecurity (CC), Cisco CyberOps Associate

---

## ðŸŸ¡ Mid-Level Roles *(Specialisation & Tactical Execution)*

Requires deeper technical expertise and practical experience:

- Cybersecurity Analyst  
- Cybersecurity Consultant  
- Penetration & Vulnerability Tester  

> ðŸ§ª Tools to Master: Wireshark, Nmap, Metasploit, Nessus  
> ðŸ“œ Recommended Certs: CySA+, PenTest+, CEH

---

## ðŸ”´ Advanced-Level Roles *(Strategic & Leadership Positions)*

Strategic roles focused on architecture, governance, and team leadership:

- Cybersecurity Manager / Administrator  
- Cybersecurity Engineer  
- Cybersecurity Architect  

> ðŸ›¡ï¸ Governance Tie-In: Align with frameworks like NIST, ISO 27001, and GDPR  
> ðŸ“œ Recommended Certs: CISSP, CISM, CISA

---

